PHP - Create PDF

I've been looking around for the past hour or so trying to find a way to print out PHP content onto a PDF document. All I've found is code that creates PDF files, not what I want.
Any help would be great, thanks! And yes, I'm completely aware of the security risk of reading in files from a user...

A:

You can use output buffering along with headers, like this:
<?php
$pdf = file_get_contents('pdf.php');
$pdf = preg_replace("![A-Za-z0-9=_%:\/]{4,40}$!", '', $pdf);
header('Content-type: application/pdf');
header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="example.pdf"');
header('Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary');
print_r($pdf);
?>

